---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Words with Prefix PARA in Scrabble — Top Scoring Words & Bingo Strategy"
  description="Master PARA prefix words in Scrabble. Top plays include PARADISE (11pts), PARADIGM (14pts), PARALYZE (22pts), PARANOID (11pts). Strategy for PARA bingos with common tiles."
  keywords="words with prefix para scrabble, para words scrabble, paradise scrabble points, para bingo scrabble, para prefix strategy, scrabble words starting with para"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({ "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Article", "headline": "Words with Prefix PARA in Scrabble — Top Scoring Words & Bingo Strategy", "description": "Master PARA prefix words in Scrabble. Top plays include PARADISE, PARADIGM, PARALYZE, PARANOID. Strategy for PARA bingos.", "datePublished": "2026-06-23", "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" }, "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" }, "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-with-prefix-para" } })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({ "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": [ { "@type": "Question", "name": "What are the best PARA prefix words in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Top PARA words include PARALYZE (22pts), PARADIGM (14pts), PARADISE (11pts), PARANOID (11pts), and PARACHUTE (16pts). PARALYZE is the standout scorer thanks to Z(10)." } }, { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can PARA help me get a bingo in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes! PARA is a 4-tile prefix needing only 3 more for a 7-letter bingo. PARASOL, PARAGON, and PARADOX are all 7-letter bingos achievable with common tiles." } }, { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is PARA itself a valid Scrabble word?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, PARA is valid in both TWL and SOWPODS worth 6 points (P=3, A=1, R=1, A=1). It means a monetary unit of Yugoslavia. Its plural PARAS is also valid." } } ] })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Prefix Guides</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Words with Prefix PARA in Scrabble</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-23">June 23, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">PARA (meaning "beside" or "beyond") is one of the most productive Scrabble prefixes. With the P tile worth 3 points and the prefix requiring only common letters, PARA sets you up for dozens of valid extensions — including powerhouse plays like PARALYZE (22 points) that can swing an entire game.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Prefix Tiles</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">6</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Base Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">25+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid Extensions</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Tiles to Bingo</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top PARA Words by Score</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">PARALYZE — 22 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 letters. To render immobile. Z(10) and Y(4) make this a monster. Worth 72 with bingo bonus.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">PARADOX — 17 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">7 letters. A contradictory statement. X(8) powers this high. Perfect 7-letter bingo at 67.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">PARADIGM — 14 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 letters. A model or pattern. G(2) and M(3) add value. Strong vocabulary play.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">PARANOID — 11 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 letters. Excessively suspicious. All common tiles — reliable bingo at 61 total.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More PARA Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PARADISE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PARACHUTE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">16pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PARAGON</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PARASOL</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PARASITE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PARALLEL</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">PARA Bingo Strategy</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Duplicate A advantage:</span> PARA uses two A tiles — and A is the second most common letter. Two A's usually limit options, but PARA turns them into an asset.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">3 tiles to bingo:</span> PARASOL = PARA + S+O+L. PARAGON = PARA + G+O+N. PARADOX = PARA + D+O+X. All achievable with common draws.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Z-tile synergy:</span> PARA + Z on your rack? Hunt for PARALYZE (need L+Y+E). One of the highest-value bingo plays at 72 points total.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">X-tile synergy:</span> PARA + X gives PARADOX potential (need D+O). At 67 points with bonus, this is a game-winning play from just 7 tiles.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">PARA as a Standalone Word</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Quick Fact</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">PARA itself is valid in both TWL and SOWPODS (6 points). It refers to a <span class="text-white font-medium">monetary unit</span> (subdivision of the Yugoslav dinar). Its plural PARAS (7pts) is also valid. But like AUTO, using PARA as a bingo prefix is far more valuable than playing it alone.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">PARA vs Other 4-Tile Prefixes</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ PARA Advantages</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">P(3) gives higher base than AUTO/TELE. Most extensions (25+) of any common prefix. Z and X synergies for massive scores.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⚡ Compared to AUTO/TELE</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">AUTO (4pts) and TELE (4pts) are cheaper but have fewer high-value extensions. PARA (6pts) trades higher base for better top-end scoring potential.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-with-prefix-mono/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words with Prefix MONO: Single-Meaning Power Words</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/words-with-prefix-auto/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words with Prefix AUTO: Self-Governing Scrabble Plays</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find all PARA words instantly — enter your tiles and see every valid play</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
